    "en": {
      "title": "Govt. employees leave form for foreign employment reduced to 2 pages",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ministry of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Local Government and Provincial Councils has decided to reduce the pages of the form that employees have to submit when they seek to leave for employment abroad.",
        "The number of pages of the application form has been reduced to two pages from four according to the ministry.",
        "This decision has been made following the instructions of the subject minister, Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena.",
        "The cost of printing the application form is said to be reduced by 50 per cent through this move. The cost of printing the application forms is said to be high, as many workers attached to the institutions under the ministry are seeking leave for employment abroad.",
        "The new two-page form has already been sent to the Department of State Printing."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
